He had been spared the long trip to Istanbul for the Europa League tie against Besiktas in midweek and the benefits were obvious as his passing and movement tormented Pellegrini’s side.

‘It was a brilliant result and an equally brilliant performance,’ Rodgers enthused.

What made Liverpool’s performance all the more meritorious, according to Rodgers, was that their preparations had been disrupted by the Europa League.

They only returned to Merseyside at 4.30am on Friday yet finished the stronger side on Sunday.

‘It is a big win but we still have a lot of games to go,’ said Rodgers. ‘But it is a significant win for us, another three points. 

'To prepare yourself for a game against the champions is no mean feat. You have to take your hat off to them, the performance was at a real top level.’

